# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Brewzy Operations — Firebase configuration
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Create a free Firebase project at https://console.firebase.google.com
# 2. Add a "Web app" to it, then copy the config values it shows you.
# 3. Copy this file to ".env" (or ".env.local") and paste your values below.
#
# NOTE: These Firebase web keys are NOT secret — they ship in the client
# bundle by design. Your data is protected by Firestore security rules +
# anonymous auth, not by hiding these values.

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
